    "Occupier",
    "The development must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date hereof.\r\rReason: To comply with Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, as amended.",
    "All external facing materials, treatments and finishes shall be similar to those of the original building. Where this is not possible the type and treatment of the materials to be used shall be agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to any above ground works being carried out.  \r\rReason: To ensure that the extension harmonises with the existing building and to ensure compliance with Policy 28 of the Sutton Local Plan 2018.\r",
    "The use of raised patio area shall not commence until the 1.7 metres high screens as measured from the floor level of the raised patio and terrace area on the side boundaries as indicated on the approved drawing No's A-BR-P Revision 03, A-BR-S-B-C Revision 03 and A-BR-S-A Revision 02 have been installed and they shall be permanently retained as such thereafter.\r\rReason: In order to ensure that the use of the raised timber decking area as terrace would not result in overlooking and any subsequent loss of privacy to neighbouring residents in accordance with Policy 29 of the Sutton Local Plan 2018.\r",
    "The development must be carried out in accordance with the provisions of the Fire Statement compliant with Policy D12(A) by Fire Safety South East Date 11/02/2025 in compliance under Policy D12 unless otherwise approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority.\r\rReason: To ensure that the development incorporates the necessary fire safety measures in accordance with the Mayor's London Plan Policy D12."
